# =============================================================================
# Personal OS API — Jenkins Secret File
# Credential ID: env-personal-os-api-dev | env-personal-os-api-staging | env-personal-os-api-prod
#
# Canonical template: backend/.env.prod (copy that file, replace CHANGE_ME_* secrets)
#
# Values with spaces or $ MUST be quoted, e.g. POSTGRES_DATABASE_PASSWORD="your$pass"
# Jenkins deploy reads POSTGRES_* via grep (does not shell-source the file).
# Accepted keys: POSTGRES_DATABASE_USER | POSTGRES_USER, etc.
# Used by Jenkinsfile for:
#   • personal-os-api-app-{env}  (--env-file)
#   • personal-os-pg-{env}       (POSTGRES_DATABASE_* at deploy)
#
# AI (OpenRouter + DeepSeek): set OPENROUTER_API_KEY in the secret file.
# See backend/.env.example for OPENROUTER_MODEL, OPENAI_EMBEDDING_MODEL, EMBEDDING_*.
#
# Docker network shared with fash-api-gateway (Kong upstream).
# ENVIRONMENT=prod but gateway still on dev → set dev network explicitly:
# IOT_PUBLIC_NET=iot-public-net-dev
# =============================================================================
